The paper deals with the design of transceiver pairs for block-by-block communication systems, which is a topic that falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and communication (cs.COMM) sub-categories. The use of decision feedback detection also suggests a potential connection to the signal processing (cs.SI) and networking (cs.NI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper's focus on optimizing performance metrics such as bit error rate and mutual information suggests a potential connection to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category.
